parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The frame rust and corrosion can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The frame is rusted or corroded
the rear gas tank strap is corroded
the frame is severely rusted and can split in half
the chassis is not in good condition
the rust has eaten up a large part of the chassis beam
the frame is rusted beyond being repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Issues and Lack of Notification
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of notification and resolution of the recall issues can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded due to the frame rust and corrosion.
symptoms: The owner was not notified of the recall
the recall was expired
the dealer refused to inspect or repair the vehicle
the manufacturer refused to assist with the repair
the vehicle was not repaired despite multiple attempts to contact the dealer and manufacturer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of assistance from Toyota can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded due to the frame rust and corrosion.
symptoms: Toyota refused to assist with the repair
Toyota refused to recognize the issue
Toyota only referred to an unrelated extended warranty
Toyota denied any further assistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
even when the driver's foot is not on the accelerator pedal. The acceleration may occur when the vehicle is stationary
in motion
or when the driver is attempting to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic engine RPM and acceleration can cause the vehicle to lurch forward or backward, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine RPM increases suddenly and unexpectedly
causing the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate rapidly. This may occur when the vehicle is stationary
in motion
or when the driver is attempting to brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Accelerator Pedal Interference
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interference between the brake pedal and accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The driver's foot may accidentally press the accelerator pedal while attempting to brake
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly. The close proximity of the brake and accelerator pedals may contribute to this issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become structurally unsound, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rust spots on the frame
holes in the frame
corrosion on the undercarriage
rusted brake lines
rusted rear bumper cross arm
and severely corroded passenger's side frame
driver's side frame
and subframe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The paint defects and rust can cause the vehicle's body to deteriorate, leading to safety issues and compromised structural integrity.
symptoms: Peeling paint
rust spots on the roof
corrosion on the body
and premature paint failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusted frame can lead to structural failure, causing loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Rust and corrosion on the frame
especially behind the front passenger side wheel
and near the passenger door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive shaft and U-joints can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vibration
noise
and failure of the drive shaft and U-joints
leading to loss of acceleration and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and clutch can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting gears
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
and unusual engine RPM behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and shaking can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vibration and shaking of the vehicle
especially at low speeds
and difficulty shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected acceleration and brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Unexpected acceleration
brake failure
and unusual engine RPM behavior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering intermediate shaft can cause the steering to stiffen unexpectedly, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering becomes stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
the steering wheel sticks or binds
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering to become difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power steering fails
the steering becomes difficult or hard to turn
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the power steering system to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The frame is rusting
the power steering system fails
and the vehicle is difficult to control.
